```julia
using Dates

function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int=3)
    return dt + Hour(bump)
end

# Test the function
dt = DateTime(2022, 1, 1, 12, 0, 0)
@show timezone_bumper(dt)
@show timezone_bumper(dt, 5)

# This will throw an error
d = Date(2022, 1, 1)
@show timezone_bumper(d)
```

This function uses Julia's Dates module to add a specified number of hours to a DateTime object. It defaults to adding 3 hours if no value is provided. If a Date object is passed to the function, it will throw an error because the function is only defined for DateTime objects.
